      <section id="id4256109">
        <title>[LO 4.4.1, 3.1.1]</title>
        <list id="id2162252" list-type="enumerated" number-style="arabic">
          <item>Write a descriptive paragraph/poem (± 70 words) of an animal in a specific setting.</item>
        </list>
        <para id="id4074465">Choose imaginative and vivid ADJECTIVES to describe what you see.</para>
        <para id="id4285935">Use powerful VERBS to describe movement and sound.</para>
        <para id="id2464595">Start with a striking sentence.</para>
        <para id="id4496344">Possible template to use:</para>
        <list id="id2158830" list-type="bulleted">
          <item>Striking first line</item>
          <item>Some adjectives to use</item>
          <item>Some verbs to use</item>
          <item>Rough draft(s)</item>
          <item>Edited version</item>
        </list>
        <para id="id2195120">2. Now find a poem about an animal that appeals to you and come and read it to the class.</para>
        <para id="id2275013">It is important that you manage to convey what the poet is trying to say. Remember: It is the <emphasis effect="italics">message </emphasis>of the poem that is important – so you need not feel shy or embarrassed. </para>
      </section>
